  "text": "The supersymmetric quantum mechanics takes place on the moduli space M which is a Kahler manifold. The Hilbert space is the collection of (p, q) differential forms on M, and the 4 supercharges are represented by ∂,∂, ∂ * ,∂ * . Supersymmetric ground states exist -they are the harmonic forms. These states constitute a representation of SU(2) p in the following way: denote by J 3 , J + , J − the standard SU(2) generators. J 3 acts by multiplying a (p, q) harmonic form by (p + q − dim C M)/2, while J + , J − act by a wedge product or contraction with the Kahler form. The harmonic forms split into a number of SU(2) representations, the highest of which is [CITATION_1] .",
